Techical Notes

  1. Data include nursing home beds, pediatric beds, behavioral intervention beds, ventilator beds, scatter ventilator beds, traumatic brain injury beds, neurodegenerative disease beds; exclude pediatric ventilator beds, dialysis station beds, and adult day health care slots.
  2. Spending data represent fee-for-service spending only.
  3. Census data represent all occupied beds, regardless of payor type.
  4. Beds = The number of Residential Beds the facility is approved to operate.
  5. Beds Available = Available Residential Beds reported by facility. This figure should include any licensed beds that are not operational.
  6. Census (aka “Occupied Beds”) = (Beds) - (Beds Available).
  7. End of Period Census The total number of occupied beds at the end of the reporting period. For completed fiscal years, this represents the census at the end of the year. For partial fiscal years, it reflects the census as of the most recent reporting date.
